    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "I hear you on the emissions part, but I’m seeing a lot of pushback from people saying this is basically just a tax on people who can't afford to live in the city and have to commute from further out. If the \"non-negotiable\" environmental benefits are basically guaranteed, don't the social equity concerns just become an obstacle that needs to be managed rather than a reason to reconsider the whole thing?",
