      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "You are absolutely right that equity concerns are a major hurdle, but they are not a reason to abandon the policy; they are a critical design flaw that must be fixed. If the revenue from congestion pricing is ring-fenced to subsidize affordable housing and public transit, the financial burden can be effectively neutralized while still achieving those non-negotiable environmental goals. Ignoring the social impact would be a strategic error that could doom the project, whereas addressing it head-on transforms the policy from a punitive tax into a necessary investment in both climate stability and social justice.",
